Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Halve the @Baking Potato{2}(lengthways) and pop them onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Rub the oil over the potatoes, then lay them cut-side down.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until tender and a knife slips in easily, ~{30-40%minutes}.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{60%grams}.

Finely chop the @Chives{1%bunch}(finely chopped) (use scissors if easier). Roughly chop the @Pecan Nut Halves{25%grams}.

Quarter, core and thinly slice the @Apple{1}(thinly sliced) (no need to peel). Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

== Rarebit Sauce ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced Chorizo{90%grams} and fry until it starts to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and fry for a further ~{30%seconds}.

Stir the @Creme Fraiche{150%grams}, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%grams}, @Worcester Sauce{15%grams}, @Water for the Sauce{100%ml} and two thirds of the @Wholegrain Mustard{17%grams} (add less if you'd prefer) into the chorizo. Simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir through the cheese until melted. Taste and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick. Remove from the heat and set aside.

== Apple and Honey Dressing ==

In a medium #bowl{}, add the sliced apple, remaining mustard, @Honey{1%tbsp} and @Olive Oil for the Dressing{1%tbsp}.

Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then toss to combine. Set aside.

== Assembly ==

When the potatoes are ready, reheat your rarebit sauce.

Remove the potatoes from the oven and use a #fork{} to lightly mash a spoonful of sauce into the flesh.

Toss the @Baby Leaf Mix{50%grams} with the apple and honey dressing.

Share your baked potatoes between your plates. Spoon over the remaining rarebit sauce, then sprinkle over the chives.

Serve the apple salad alongside topped with a sprinkling of pecans.

Enjoy!